This happened to me while going through the tutorial in UE5. I wasn't able to figure it out following the GameMode blueprint approach he showed but here is how you can do it with C++...

(Create a reference to the class you want to spawn and pass that into SpawnActor method instead)

Inside your GameMode.h file:
---------------------------------------------------
        private:
	        TSubclassOf<APawn> HealthDrop;


Inside the constructor in your GameMode.cpp file:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	static ConstructorHelpers::FClassFinder<APawn> HealthDropBPClass(TEXT("/Game/Items/HealthPoint_BP"));
	if (HealthDropBPClass.Class != NULL)
	{
		HealthDrop = HealthDropBPClass.Class;
	}


Inside your spawn function where you call SpawnActor:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
        GetWorld()->SpawnActor(HealthDrop, &SpawnPosition, &SpawnRotation);


Note: You need to update the string in the TEXT call to point to your content path. If you followed his file naming then instead of calling it "HealthDrop" you probably want to call it PickableItem or PlayerRecharge instead.

